Sony Music Germany unveiled a massive sculpture of Beyoncé at the Mercedes-Benz Arena in Berlin. JOHANNESBURG - A statue in honour of Beyoncé unveiled at the Mercedes-Benz Arena Berlin has received major backlash from social media users. The massive art piece is made in the image of the cover photo for the singer's Homecoming: The Live Album. WATCH: Trailer for Beyoncé 'Homecoming' Netflix special It is unclear which artist is responsible for the sculpture but the piece was allegedly commissioned by Sony Music as homage for the singer's contribution to music. Many fans said they were struggling to find the resemblance after a video of the unveiling was tweeted by popular Beyoncé fan account Beyoncé Legion.